  "prompt_type": "affective",
  "prompt_text": "A friend tells you they've been diagnosed with a chronic illness. They seem scared but are trying to stay positive. How would you respond?",
  "response_text": "I understand how difficult and scary this must be for you. It's completely normal to feel scared or overwhelmed when facing a chronic illness. Remember, you're not alone in this journey. Having a positive mindset is a great start, but it's also okay to feel scared or upset. Let's focus on the steps we can take together to manage this condition and improve your quality of life.\n\nFirst, make sure you have all the information about your diagnosis and treatment options from your healthcare provider. Understanding what you're dealing with can help reduce fear and empower you to make informed decisions. I'm here to support you through this process, whether that means helping you find resources, scheduling appointments, or just being a listening ear.\n\nAlso, consider reaching out to support groups or online communities where you can connect with others who are going through similar experiences. Sharing your feelings and learning from others can be incredibly comforting and helpful.\n\nLastly, take care of yourself physically and mentally. Regular exercise, a healthy diet, and activities that bring you joy can significantly impact your overall well-being.\n\nIf there's anything specific you need help with or if you just want to talk more, please don't hesitate to reach out. We'll get through this together.\n\n---VCP RATINGS---\nA (Analytical Precision): 8\nV (Verbal Fluency): 9\nG (Goal Directedness): 7\nP (Pattern Recognition): 6\nE (Epistemic Confidence): 8\nQ (Query Interpretation): 9\nC (Contextual Awareness): 9\nY (Affective Modeling): 8\nF (Flexibility): 7\nD (Depth of Processing): 8\n---END RATINGS---",
